Same thing happened to me when I was buying a fungi .. I was on one of my mules and this person asks me how much I am paying, and tells me "that's a little low, but I will do it only under one condition - that you give the money to this toon instead of my main, so I don't have to deal with finding someone to transfer for me to buy stuff for this toon".. I laughed, and logged off, then logged on another mule .. I started auctioning to buy a fungi from there, and somebody else sends me a tell (had to be the same person) saying almost the same thing, and that I can trust him because he has a level 60 warrior in House Calenture .. This really got me laughing, 1) House Calenture had been disbanded for 2 weeks already, and 2) Would I really trust someone from there??<p>How can people be so lame .. The sad thing is that they have scammed several people the same way, and most of the time, the GM's won't do anything about it.<p>--------------------</p><p>Aandiian<br />60 Warder<br />Legend of Marr</p>
